last_episode_to_air.name: Please Shine Down on Me
last_episode_to_air.overview: Murphy copes by distracting herself with a new motivation: getting even. Felix attempts to help her find other ways to deal with her emotions, but like anything with Murphy, it's an uphill battle. Josh is smug as he slowly puts together how the night unfolded, until he realized that it's not over yet.

name: In the Dark
overview: Murphy is a flawed and irreverent woman who just happens to be blind and is the only “witness” to the murder of her drug-dealing friend, Tyson. When the police dismiss her story, she sets out with her dog, Pretzel, to find the killer while also managing her colorful dating life and the job she hates at Guiding Hope, the guide-dog school owned by her overprotective parents.

seasons.name: Season 3
seasons.overview: In season three, Murphy and her best friend, Jess, along with their annoying friend Felix, and Murphy's ex-boyfriend, Max, find themselves faced with yet another dilemma - how to avoid getting caught for murder. But it turns out, the authorities aren’t the only ones after them - they’re also wanted by high powered drug kingpin Josiah, so they seek the help of Darnell and his buddy Trey to keep out of his crosshairs.

episodes.name: Pilot
episodes.overview: Murphy is a hard-living, hard-drinking, disaffected twenty-something with a penchant for cigarettes and casual sex. She’s also blind.

episodes.name: Mommy Issues
episodes.overview: After Murphy’s latest one night stand calls her “Mommy,” she develops a rather unexpected lead in Tyson’s case. Meanwhile, Chloe thinks it’s time for her father Dean to start a dating profile. Lastly, Murphy helps Jess pick out a special gift for her girlfriend Vanessa.

episodes.name: The Big Break
episodes.overview: Murphy enlists an unwitting Felix to help her organize an outreach presentation at Fairview High so she can do some digging around to try and locate Tysons girlfriend Kira. When the presentation goes awry, Murphy and Felix take a smoke break under the bleachers and have their first heart-to-heart. Meanwhile, Dean does his best to be there for Chloe as she experience’s a rite of passage.

episodes.name: The Graduate
episodes.overview: Murphy discovers she may not have known Tyson as well as she thought she did. Meanwhile, it’s puppy graduation day at Guiding Hope, and one of the foster’s is having a hard time letting go.

episodes.name: The Feels
episodes.overview: Jess reluctantly agrees to let Murphy go alone with Max  on a day trip. While traveling, Murphy has flashback of memories of Tyson. Meanwhile, Jess and Joy (Kathleen York) realize they may have more in common than they thought.

episodes.name: Tyson
episodes.overview: Murphy, unable to deal with things, begins to push everyone away, including Max. Meanwhile, Murphy and Jess have a heart-to-heart.

episodes.name: The One That Got Away
episodes.overview: While hanging out with Max in his food truck, Murphy is shocked to hear a familiar voice screaming outside; Murphy offers to watch Chloe so Dean can go on a date, but things get a little crazy after she does the one thing he asks her not to do. Lastly, Murphy's worlds of Max and Darnell and Guiding Hope begin to collide.

episodes.name: Jessica Rabbit
episodes.overview: Murphy finally starts opening up to Max. Meanwhile, Murphy, Max and Darnell step up to help Jess. Lastly, Felix  makes an interesting decision.

episodes.name: Deal or No Deal
episodes.overview: With Jess focusing all of her attention on Vanessa, Murphy begins to feel neglected. To make matters worse, tensions begin to rise between her and Max. Meanwhile, Jules is forced to make a quick decision.

episodes.name: Bait and Switch
episodes.overview: Murphy and Jess are both going through similar situations, but they are handling things very differently. Meanwhile, Felix and Jess share a beautiful moment together.

episodes.name: I Woke Up Like This
episodes.overview: Murphy and Jess borrow the Guiding Hope van to search for Max, leaving Felix in a precarious position. Meanwhile, Dean receives some surprising news.

episodes.name: Rollin' With the Homies
episodes.overview: It’s Murphy’s first birthday since Tyson was killed and she is feeling more isolated than ever.

episodes.name: It's Always Been You
episodes.overview: Things begin to take an interesting turn between Murphy and Dean. Season finale.

episodes.name: All About the Benjamin
episodes.overview: Murphy, Jess and Felix must act quickly to devise a plan that will keep them out of Nia's crosshairs and, possibly, save Guiding Hope in the process.

episodes.name: Cross My Heart and Hope to Lie
episodes.overview: Murphy gets a surprise visit; Felix, Jess and Murphy work on a plan to cover up their new "business"; Darnell's visit to Nia takes an unexpected turn; Dean gets a new mission.

episodes.name: Son of a Gun
episodes.overview: Murphy is forced to turn her attention from Max  when Guiding Hope’s monetary surplus puts them on the radar of IRS agent Josh. Meanwhile, Jess’s interest is piqued by a new employee and Felix decides to take matters into his own hands. Dean gets closer to information he can use against Nia and Darnell  explores his options.

episodes.name: Deal Me In
episodes.overview: Murphy seeks to help Max out of a life-or-death situation, while Dean leverages them against each other in an attempt to fix his own bad circumstances. Felix finds difficulty juggling his dating life with his dealing life, while Jess is happily distracted by a new romance. Darnell tries a new gig, but his loyalty to Murphy and Max keeps him entangled in Nia’s web.

episodes.name: The Unusual Suspects
episodes.overview: Murphy's choices plunge the Guiding Hope crew deeper into Nia's game, as Jess continues to grow suspicious of the closed-door meetings between Felix and Murphy. Dean tries to keep Chloe away from Murphy.

episodes.name: The Truth Hurts
episodes.overview: While Murphy and Felix juggle their personal extracurricular activities with the demands of drug dealing, Jess finds herself inextricably in Nia’s crosshairs. Trey has Darnell’s back, and Max finds himself at the end of a rope. Josh continues to seek Murphy’s assistance with his challenging circumstances, while Dean contends with Chloe’s newfound rebelliousness.

episodes.name: The Straw That Broke the Camel's Back
episodes.overview: Murphy’s preoccupation with helping Max - whose luck continues to spiral – forces her to take more extreme risks. Felix is forced to contend with issues at Guiding Hope, while Jess struggles as all her relationships are tested. Meanwhile, Chloe meets Dean’s new partner, Gene, who shares information that feeds into her growing suspicions about her father.

episodes.name: Codependence Day
episodes.overview: Murphy convinces Jess to help with a drug mission; Felix finds himself in a legal predicament; Dean's partner Gene begins showing some real talent on the job, giving Dean a lead that could unravel Murphy's plans.

episodes.name: How to Succeed in Business Without Really Dying
episodes.overview: When Murphy and Felix concoct a new plan to destroy Nia, Murphy's friendship with Josh proves to be more beneficial than she expected. In need of some space from Murphy, Jess makes a bold move with Sterling. Dean runs into issues at work, and Max gets an unexpected visitor.

episodes.name: The Last Dance
episodes.overview: Murphy and Felix swing for the fences when they attempt to execute the plan to end their arrangement with Nia. Finding himself in dire circumstances, Dean seeks the help of a former colleague. Max does the unthinkable.

episodes.name: Bad People
episodes.overview: With stakes high for everyone, Murphy, Jess, Felix, Max and Dean must each contend with the fallout following an attempt to cut off Nia's supply and take her down.

episodes.name: Where Have You Ben?
episodes.overview: with Nia's entire shipment missing and the Guiding Hope crew under the gun to deliver it, Murphy, Jess Felix and Max will stop at nothing to sniff out the stash. In the meantime, Dean as his own plans for the misplaced goods, while Gene visits Darnell  and uncovers some shocking information

episodes.name: My Pride and Joy
episodes.overview: A deep betrayal leads to severe consequences, which causes devastating outcomes for the people involved.

episodes.name: Hanging by a Thread
episodes.overview: With Nia dead and Josh aware of their involvement in the biggest case of his career, Murphy, Jess, Felix and Max are forced to make some life-changing decisions. Meanwhile, Officer Gene Clemens suspects something is awry within the department and forms an unlikely partnership with Josh.

episodes.name: I Know What You Did Last Night
episodes.overview: Murphy, Jess, Felix and Max begin a long and arduous journey as they attempt to stay one step ahead of Josh and Clemens.

episodes.name: Somewhere Over the Border
episodes.overview: Murphy experiences being truly alone in an unfamiliar place and begins to realize how helpless she is without her friends.

episodes.name: Safe and Sound
episodes.overview: With Murphy still on the run, Josiah enlists Darnell to try and track her down.

episodes.name: Planes, Trains & Automobiles
episodes.overview: Murphy reaches out to an unlikely source for help in getting to Jess but when Trey makes other plans, the whole thing blows up in their faces.

episodes.name: Arcade Fire
episodes.overview: Murphy’s desperate attempt to save Jess lands her in deeper trouble. A disagreement between Gene and Josh is not without its consequences.

episodes.name: Pretty In Pink
episodes.overview: Murphy, Felix and Max look to Josiah for answers about Jess.

episodes.name: Power Trip
episodes.overview: Things get awkward when Murphy and her friends ride out the storm together.

episodes.name: Excess Baggage
episodes.overview: When Murphy starts to spin out, Felix takes matters into his own hands.

episodes.name: Home Run
episodes.overview: Feeling isolated and alone, Murphy seeks comfort in the familiar but sometimes things do change, and she is forced to fend for herself.

episodes.name: Match Point
episodes.overview: With the walls closing in, Murphy and Trey make a desperate move.

episodes.name: Do You Hear What I Hear?
episodes.overview: As Murphy closes in on finding out what happened to Jess, Clemens and Josh move one step closer to finding Murphy.

episodes.name: Expectation is the Root of All Heartache
episodes.overview: Murphy finally learns the truth about what happened to Jess and it forces her to take a closer look at who she herself has become. Season Finale.

3.name: Season 3
3.overview: In season three, Murphy and her best friend, Jess, along with their annoying friend Felix, and Murphy's ex-boyfriend, Max, find themselves faced with yet another dilemma - how to avoid getting caught for murder. But it turns out, the authorities aren’t the only ones after them - they’re also wanted by high powered drug kingpin Josiah, so they seek the help of Darnell and his buddy Trey to keep out of his crosshairs.

episodes.name: Bail's In Your Court
episodes.overview: Murphy is having a tough time adjusting to life in prison with unexpected dangers looming large. Meanwhile, Max accompanies Leslie and Felix to an interesting afternoon with their grandmother.

episodes.name: No Cane Do
episodes.overview: Murphy has to get creative if she is going to stay alive, meanwhile, Felix comes up with a plan to help his friend.

episodes.name: If Books Could Kill
episodes.overview: Murphy accidentally sets off a chain of events that have near fatal consequences for Felix. Meanwhile, Leslie's quick thinking buys everyone a little breathing room.

episodes.name: Hard Pill to Swallow
episodes.overview: Gene and Josh take a swing at tying Murphy to their latest case and end up with something completely unexpected meanwhile, Felix tricks Max into revealing what he has been hiding and Leslie has to improvise when a plan she put into motion goes off course.

episodes.name: The Trial of Murphy Mason (1)
episodes.overview: Murphy’s trial date has arrived and she must face all the ghosts of her past that have come forward as witnesses against her and the secrets that are revealed along the way. Meanwhile, the trial also means a complicated reunion for Felix.

episodes.name: The Trial of Murphy Mason (2)
episodes.overview: Truths are uncovered as Murphy's trial continues. Meanwhile, the police continue to search for evidence.

episodes.name: C.I. Was Right
episodes.overview: Murphy follows through on the deal she made and finds herself partnered up with someone who she'd rather not have to spend time with. Meanwhile, Max is left reeling after the mess he made during Murphy's trial.

episodes.name: Tequila Mockingbird
episodes.overview: Tensions run high when Murphy's plans hit a bump in the road. Josh's vendetta against Murphy grows with the help of a new friend.

episodes.name: Center of Gravity
episodes.overview: Murphy and Max have a long overdue conversation. Darnell's paranoia turns into fear when everything starts crumbling.

episodes.name: No Time to Spare
episodes.overview: Murphy and Darnell come face to face with the source of their problems and Max and Gene get pulled into the mess. As his condition worsens, Josh's bad blood with Murphy gets the best of him.

episodes.name: The Deep End
episodes.overview: Josh's persistence to bring Murphy down motivates everyone to pull a plan together. Murphy asks Felix for a favor and Darnell learns some intriguing information about the team behind Bolt.

episodes.name: Going Up
episodes.overview: Max and Murphy make plans for the future, and everything seems to be going according to plan at the fundraiser with Murphy and Darnell posing as the un-happy couple. Meanwhile, Josh concocts his own plan and inserts himself in the middle of everything.

episodes.name: Please Shine Down on Me
episodes.overview: Murphy copes by distracting herself with a new motivation: getting even. Felix attempts to help her find other ways to deal with her emotions, but like anything with Murphy, it's an uphill battle. Josh is smug as he slowly puts together how the night unfolded, until he realized that it's not over yet.
